SIMPLE: lodgment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lodgment
<hw>Lodg"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>lodgement</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>logement</ets>. See
<er>Lodge</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
lodging, or the state of being lodged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Any particle which is of size enough to make a <qex>lodgment</qex>
afterwards in the small arteries.</q> <rj><qau>Paley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lodging place; a room.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An accumulation or collection of something deposited
in a place or remaining at rest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The occupation and holding of a
position, as by a besieging party; an instrument thrown up in a captured
position; <as>as, to effect a <ex>lodgment</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lodicule</ent>⟦br⟧
